    bytecode  
    translation  
  • Classes in bytecode used by bytecode 
    Class and Description
    ArithmeticBinOpBytecode
    A bytecode that computes a binary arithmetic operation on the top two elements of the stack.
    BinOpBytecode
    A bytecode that performs a binary operation on the top two elements of the stack.
    BranchingBytecode
    A bytecode with two subsequent bytecodes.
    BranchingComparisonBytecode
    A bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack.
    BranchingConstantComparisonBytecode
    A bytecode that compares the top element of the stack with a constant.
    BranchingNumericalComparisonBytecode
    A bytecode that applies a numerical comparison on the top two elements of the stack.
    Bytecode
    A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language.
    BytecodeList
    A list of Kitten bytecodes.
    CALL
    A bytecode that calls a method of a receiver.
    ComparisonBinOpBytecode
    A bytecode that computes a binary comparison operation between the top two elements of the stack.
    ComparisonNumericalBinOpBytecode
    A bytecode that computes a numerical binary comparison operation between the top two elements of the stack.
    FieldAccessBytecode
    A bytecode that accesses a field.
    FinalBytecode
    A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language with no subsequent bytecode.
    NonBranchingBytecode
    A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language with one or no subsequent bytecode.
    NonCallingBytecode
    A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language that does not call any method or constructor or block of call.
    NonCallingSequentialBytecode
    A sequential bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language that does not call any piece of code.
    SequentialBytecode
    A sequential bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language, that is, a bytecode that never gives rise to a branching when executed and that has always a successor bytecode.
